      {
        "id": 2402515,
        "name": "Ben B Floyd",
        "username": "Ben_B_Floyd",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ben_b_floyd/{size}/3040_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-04-23T03:03:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I tried to talk them into another Loire white, but once they saw the \u201815 Vatan, they begged and pleaded.</p>\n<p>Not sure if this was a baby kill or a reality pill.</p>\n<p>I usually sit on my Vatans as well as my Cotats for a while before opening.  Although this was softer than any prematurely opened cuvee of Cotat I\u2019ve ever experienced, it was still not that expressive.  Just \u201cOK\u201d with my (perfectly) grilled fresh black cod course.  After all the fuss, we didn\u2019t even finish the bottle.</p>\n<p>This was purchased at a significant bump to prior vintages\u2019 pricing.  I\u2019m assuming that this is the 2015 \u201csmall producer/scarcity/currency fluctuation/3 tier system/whatever\u201d dynamic which other WB posters have suggested that we should have expected and may as well get used to going forward.</p>\n<p>Still, if I had no prior experience with this producer, I might not be a purchaser at or above this price point in the future.</p>",
